<DOC><DOCNO> AP890311-0054 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-11-89 0718EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-Obit-Melville     03-11 0146</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Obit-Melville,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Co-Star In Old `Rookies' TV Show Dies At 52</HEAD><DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Actor Sam Melville, who played Officer MikeDanko on the early 1970s television series ``The Rookies,'' died athis home of heart failure, his publicist said. He was 52.   Melville died Thursday at his Hollywood Hills home, publicistSusan Patricola said Friday. The actor had complained of chest painsrecently but otherwise had been ``the picture of health,'' she said.   In ``The Rookies,'' Melville played a green and idealistic copdedicated to more humane methods of police work. The series was onthe air from 1969 to 1972.   Melville had been a regular guest star on the old ``Gunsmoke'' TVseries. He also appeared in such motion pictures as ``BigWednesday'' and ``The Thomas Crown Affair.''   Melville is survived by his wife, Annie, his mother and fatherand two sisters.</TEXT></DOC>